    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="690"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">752.822/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-14T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Your despatch No. 490, July 18. If it should develop that the Spanish
                    representatives are in fact endeavoring to obtain a concession for an airline,
                    the Liberian Government will undoubtedly recall the provisions of the
                    confidential supplementary agreement<note n="6" xml:id="d690fn6">Exchange of
                        notes between the Liberian Secretary of State and the American Minister,
                        June 14, 1939, <ref target="frus1939v04#pg_618">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp. 618</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1939v04#pg_619">619</ref>.</note> to the Air Navigation
                    Agreement between the United States and Liberia signed June 14, 1939.<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d690fn7">Department of State Executive Agreement Series No. 166, or
                        54 Stat. (pt. 2) 2018.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Department would be glad to be informed by telegraph as to the actual status
                    and activities of the Spaniards now in Monrovia and the recognition accorded to
                    them by the Liberian Government. We have no doubt that Secretary Simpson will
                    desire to proceed most cautiously in establishing relations with the present
                    government in Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
